annotationA: GH12334p; Magnesium ion binding; holo-[acyl-carrier-protein] synthase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: protein phosphopantetheinylation; macromolecule biosynthetic process
annotationB: Bifunctional Phosphopantetheine adenylyltransferase - Dephospho-CoA kinase (Ppat-Dpck) is a bifunctional enzyme that carries out the last two steps of the canonical Coenzyme A (CoA) biosynthesis pathway. The Ppat part converts 4'-phosphopantetheine into dephospho-CoA and subsequently the Dpck part phosphorylates dephospho-CoA to form CoA
